Docker Practical: Docker Image Tag Management

Question

Create a Docker image using Ubuntu 22.04, install curl, build the image with multiple tags, verify image creation, run a container, and manage image tags.

---

Environment

Item| Value
Operating System| Windows
Terminal| PowerShell
Container Platform| Docker Desktop
Base Image| ubuntu:22.04

---

Step 1: Verify Docker Installation

Open PowerShell.

Check Docker version:

docker --version

Expected Output:

Docker version xx.xx.xx

Verify Docker service:

docker ps

---

Step 2: Create Project Directory

mkdir dockerQ3
cd dockerQ3

Verify:

pwd

Example:

C:\Users\Abhishek\dockerQ3

---

Step 3: Create Dockerfile

Create Dockerfile:

notepad Dockerfile

Add the following content:

FROM ubuntu:22.04

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl

CMD ["/bin/bash"]

Save and close.

---

Step 4: Verify Dockerfile

Display file contents:

type Dockerfile

Expected Output:

FROM ubuntu:22.04

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl

CMD ["/bin/bash"]

---

Step 5: Build Docker Image

Build image with tag:

docker build -t ubuntu:latest .

Expected Output:

Successfully built <image-id>
Successfully tagged ubuntu:latest

---

Step 6: List Docker Images

docker images

Expected Output:

REPOSITORY   TAG      IMAGE ID
ubuntu       latest   xxxxxxxx

Verify:

ubuntu:latest

exists.

---

Step 7: Run Container and Verify curl

Start container:

docker run --rm ubuntu:latest curl --version

Expected Output:

curl 7.xx.xx
Protocols: ...
Features: ...

This confirms curl was installed successfully.

---

Alternative Interactive Verification

Run container:

docker run -it ubuntu:latest bash

Inside container:

curl --version

Exit:

exit

---

Step 8: Create Additional Tags

Create tag:

docker tag ubuntu:latest ubuntu:v1.0

Create another tag:

docker tag ubuntu:latest ubuntu:stable

---

Step 9: Verify Tags

List images:

docker images

Expected Output:

REPOSITORY   TAG      IMAGE ID

ubuntu       latest   abc123
ubuntu       v1.0     abc123
ubuntu       stable   abc123

Observe:

All tags have the same IMAGE ID.

This means all tags point to the same image.

---

Step 10: Remove Tag ubuntu:stable

Remove tag:

docker rmi ubuntu:stable

Expected Output:

Untagged: ubuntu:stable

---

Step 11: Verify Remaining Tags

List images again:

docker images

Expected Output:

REPOSITORY   TAG      IMAGE ID

ubuntu       latest   abc123
ubuntu       v1.0     abc123

Verify:

ubuntu:latest
ubuntu:v1.0

still exist.

Both should have the same IMAGE ID.

---

Verification Commands

Show Images

docker images

---

Show Running Containers

docker ps

---

Show All Containers

docker ps -a

---

Inspect Image

docker inspect ubuntu:latest

---

Expected Result

Before deleting stable tag:

ubuntu:latest
ubuntu:v1.0
ubuntu:stable

After deleting stable tag:

ubuntu:latest
ubuntu:v1.0

Both tags reference the same image.

