Viva Questions

What is a Docker Image?

A read-only template used to create containers.

---

What is a Docker Container?

A running instance of a Docker image.

---

What is an Image Tag?

A label used to identify different versions of the same image.

Example:

ubuntu:latest
ubuntu:v1.0
ubuntu:stable

---

Command to Build an Image?

docker build -t ubuntu:latest .

---

Command to Create a Tag?

docker tag ubuntu:latest ubuntu:v1.0

---

Command to Remove a Tag?

docker rmi ubuntu:stable

---

Does deleting a tag delete the image?

No.

The image remains available as long as at least one tag references it.

---

Command to View Images?

docker images

---

Conclusion

Successfully created a Docker image using Ubuntu 22.04, installed curl, built the image as ubuntu:latest, verified curl installation, created additional tags ubuntu:v1.0 and ubuntu:stable, removed the stable tag, and verified that ubuntu:latest and ubuntu:v1.0 continued to reference the same Docker image.
